\pard\pardeftab720\sa280

\b\fs28 \cf0 Supporting Material\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa320

\b0\fs32 \cf0 If necessary, supporting material should be provided in a zipped folder along with the report. Supporting material should be presented in such a way as it is clearly relevant and quick to read. You should refer to supporting material in the text of your report.\
The total resulting zip file size should be no more than 20MB. For large audio and video files, provide compressed media where necessary with links to higher-quality versions online. Links to media files must be supported by compressed versions of the files, even if they are highly compressed, in order to confirm the submission date.\
If you are submitting software, bear in mind that nothing is more impressive than an application that "just works", with a clear and usable interface.\
Supporting material does not need to be your own work, but all work must be correctly and clearly credited.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280

\b\fs36 \cf0 Assessment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa320

\b0\fs32 \cf0 Reports will be assessed primarily on the basis of the quality of the work described in the report, but also on the quality of writing and presentation.\
Criteria (since reports will differ in focus, assessment criteria will be applied where applicable):\

\b Quality of research
\b0 : provide an in-depth analysis with accurate and relevant references.
\b \
Insight and quality of design
\b0 : come up with novel insights and original designs that address the problem you are working on.
\b \
Quality of problem solving and implementation
\b0 : produce advanced, robust and well structured software and hardware solutions to your design goals.
\b \
Quality of writing
\b0 : use good written English. Structure your writing clearly. Convey your message carefully and apply reasoned argument where necessary.
\b \
Clarity and quality of presentation
\b0 : be clear about your goals and your outcomes. Ensure that your report is unambiguous and understandable. Use effective visual communication where necessary.\
